14 Section 4. Section 37-39-307, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "37-39-307. Candidates for licensure or certification. (1) A person who has completed the
16 education requirements of 37-39-308, 37-39-309, 37-39-310, or 37-39-311, or 37-39-312 but who has not
17 completed the supervised work experience may apply for licensure as a candidate.
18 (2) A candidate shall submit a training and supervision plan.
19 (3) On completion of the supervised work experience, the candidate may apply to take any
20 approved examination for the licensure level OR CERTIFICATION the individual seeks to practice. Peer support
21 candidates are eligible for licensure CERTIFICATION on completion of supervised work experience without
22 examination.
23 (4) The board shall limit the number of years a person may be licensed as a candidate under this
24 section.
25 (5) On passage of an approved examination, the candidate must apply for licensure OR
26 CERTIFICATION in order to continue to practice."
