1 Section 5. Section 37-39-312, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "37-39-312. Peer support specialist license CERTIFICATION required -- qualifications. (1) A person
3 may not practice peer support unless licensed CERTIFIED under Title 37, chapter 1, and this chapter.
4 (2) An applicant for licensure CERTIFICATION as a behavioral health peer support specialist must:
5 (a) have a diagnosis from a mental health professional as having a behavioral health disorder;
6 (b) have received treatment for the diagnosed behavioral health disorder;
7 (c) be in recovery, as defined by board rule, from the behavioral health disorder; and
8 (d) have successfully completed an approved program in behavioral peer support, including an
9 ethics portion, as defined by board rule; and
10 (e) have successfully completed supervised work experience in behavioral peer support, as
11 defined by board rule. The board shall:
12 (i) provide a list of approved programs; and
13 (ii) approve content that is flexible, affordable, and inclusive of faith-based, cultural, and
14 educational programs available from national, regional, and state agencies and organizations.
15 (3) An applicant for licensure CERTIFICATION as a family peer support specialist must:
16 (a) have personal experience as the parent, guardian, or caregiver of a child under 21 years of age
17 with significant physical, developmental, or behavioral health needs; and
18 (b) have successfully completed an approved program in family peer support, including an ethics
19 portion, as defined by board rule; and
20 (c) have successfully completed supervised work experience in family peer support, as defined by
21 board rule.
22 (4) The board shall:
23 (a) provide a list of approved programs in behavioral health peer support and family peer support;
24 and
25 (b) approve content that is flexible, affordable, and inclusive of faith-based, cultural, and
26 educational programs available from national, regional, and state agencies and organizations."
